(152, '<p><strong>Read the following passage carefully!</strong></p><p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The author describes the intentions behind people’s participation in extreme sports most effectively in paragraph(s) ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Finding Detailed Information</i> yang bertujuan untuk menemukan letak informasi tentang intensi atau maksud dibalik keikutsertaan orang-orang dalam olahraga ekstrim.</p><p>Motivasi atau maksud orang-orang untuk melakukan olahraga ekstrim dapat ditemukan pada paragraf 2 pada kalimat, <i>“They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience”</i> (mereka (atlet) biasanya melakukan olahraga ekstrim untuk mendapatkan pengalaman yang membuat mereka merasa lebih hidup).</p><p>Opsi A (paragraf 1) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Paragraf 1 berisi ujaran peneliti yang mematahkan mitos olahragawan/ti sebagai pecandu adrenalin.</p><p>Opsi B (paragraf 2) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong> sesuai dengan konteks pembahasan di atas.</p><p>Opsi C (paragraf 3) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Paragraf 3 berisi pentingnya memahami motivasi dalam melakukan olahraga ekstrim.</p><p>Opsi D (paragraf 4) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Paragraf 4 membahas proses lebih lanjut dalam penelitian Professor Schweitzer.</p><p>Opsi E (paragraf 3 dan 4) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kedua paragraf tersebut tidak membahas motivasi atau maksud seseorang melakukan olahraga ekstrim.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah B.</strong></p>', 'Mudah', 'Finding Detailed Information', '2025-06-21 03:14:28', '2025-06-21 03:14:28', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
(153, '<p><strong>Read the following passage carefully!</strong></p><p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>According to Professor Schweitzer, examining people’s … behind doing extreme sports can aid us in making sense of humans.</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Vocabulary in Context</i> yang bertujuan untuk menemukan kata yang tepat untuk melengkapi kalimat rumpang di atas.</p><p>Kalimat rumpang yang berbunyi <i>“According to Professor Schweitzer, examining people’s … behind doing extreme sports can aid us in making sense of humans”</i> memiliki makna yang sama dengan kalimat pada paragraf 4, <i>“Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans”</i>. Kedua kalimat ini menyebutkan bahwa menurut Professor Schweitzer, adalah penting untuk memahami motivasi orang-orang dalam melakukan olahraga ekstrim agar kita dapat memahami manusia. Bagian rumpang pada soal memiliki posisi yang sama dengan kata <i>‘motivation’</i> (motivasi, dorongan), sehingga kita perlu menemukan sinonim dari kata tersebut.</p><p>Opsi A (keinginan, dorongan) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong> berdasarkan konteks pembahasan di atas.</p><p>Opsi B (kekhawatiran) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata pada opsi ini memiliki maksud yang berbeda dengan kata <i>‘motivation’</i>.</p><p>Opsi C (keberanian) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata <i>‘courage’</i> tidak bermakna sama dengan kata <i>‘motivation’</i>.</p><p>Opsi D (kesenangan) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata ini juga jelas bermakna berbeda dengan kata <i>‘motivation’</i>.</p><p>Opsi E (semangat, kegembiraan) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Selain karena memang bermakna berbeda, kata ini juga tidak dapat digunakan untuk mengisi bagian rumpang pada soal karena tidak sesuai dengan konteks kalimatnya.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah A.</strong></p>', 'Sedang', 'Vocabulary in Context', '2025-06-21 03:24:53', '2025-06-21 03:24:53', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
(154, '<p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>Extreme sports … allow their participants to achieve a positive state of mind and demonstrate virtues.</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Modal Auxiliary Verb</i> yang bertujuan untuk melengkapi bagian rumpang pada kalimat yang ditanyakan.</p><p>Kalimat <i>“Extreme sports … allow their participants to achieve a positive state of mind and demonstrate virtues”</i> berarti “olahraga ekstrim … memungkinkan peserta untuk mencapai pikiran yang positif dan berlaku bijak”. Kalimat ini senada dengan kalimat <i>“extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values”</i> pada paragraf 3.</p><p>Untuk melengkapi bagian rumpang pada soal, kita perlu memperhatikan peran dan dampak olahraga ekstrim kepada para pelakunya. Dari dua kalimat di atas, dapat ditarik kesimpulan bahwa olahraga ekstrim dapat, atau mampu memberikan pikiran atau pengalaman psikologis yang positif pada para pelakunya.</p><p>Opsi A (mungkin) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata <i>‘might’</i> mengimplikasikan bahwa olahraga ekstrim mungkin juga tidak dapat memberikan dampak yang positif bagi para pelakunya. Hal ini bertentangan dengan konteks kalimat pada paragraf 3 di atas.</p><p>Opsi B (seharusnya) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata <i>‘should’</i> yang menunjukkan saran tidak sesuai dengan konteks kalimat pada teks di atas.</p><p>Opsi C (harus) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata <i>‘must’</i> yang menunjukkan keharusan atau kewajiban juga tidak sesuai dengan konteks kalimat pada poin pembahasan sebelumnya.</p><p>Opsi D (akan) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong>. Kata <i>‘would’</i> menunjukkan kepastian bahwa olahraga ekstrim dapat memberikan pikiran positif pada pelakunya.</p><p>Opsi E (sebaiknya) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kata <i>‘shall’</i> tidak sesuai dengan konteks kalimat tentang dampak baik dari olahraga ekstrim kepada pelakunya.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', 'Sedang', 'Modal Auxiliary Verb', '2025-06-21 03:28:59', '2025-06-21 03:29:51', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
(155, '<p><strong>Read the following passage carefully!</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>In the passage there are statements like these:</p><p>His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the iced experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Based on the statements above, if the research team had taken a theory-based approach, they … sheer details in the extreme sports participants’ experiences.</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Conditional Sentences</i> yang bertujuan untuk melengkapi bagian rumpang pada kalimat pada soal. Untuk menjawab soal ini, kita bisa menggunakan teori pengandaian <i>(conditional sentence)</i>.</p><p>Kalimat <i>“if the research team had taken a theory-based approach, they … sheer details in the extreme sports participants’ experiences”</i> (jika tim peneliti menggunakan pendekatan berbasis teori, mereka … detail besar dalam pengalaman pelaku olahraga ekstrim) merupakan pengandaian dari kutipan teks yang diberikan pada soal yang sama—<i>”His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the iced experience of extreme sports participants”</i>.</p><p>Kalimat pengandaian yang digunakan untuk sesuatu yang telah terjadi di masa lalu dan tidak dapat diubah adalah kalimat pengandaian tipe 3. Rumus yang bisa dipakai adalah:</p><p><i><strong>If (past perfect), S + would + have + Verb 3</strong></i>, dengan subjek <i>‘they’</i>.</p><p>Opsi A (<i>will not uncover</i>/tidak akan mengungkap) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pola <i>will (not) + Verb 1</i> digunakan untuk kalimat pengandaian tipe 1 berupa sesuatu yang mungkin terjadi di masa depan.</p><p>Opsi B (<i>would not uncover</i>/tidak akan mengungkap) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pola <i>would (not) + Verb 1</i> digunakan pada kalimat pengandaian tipe 2 berupa pengandaian yang sulit terwujud di masa depan.</p><p>Opsi C (<i>will not have uncovered</i>/tidak akan pernah mengungkap) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Tidak terdapat kalimat pengandaian yang menggunakan pola <i>will (not) + have + Verb 3</i>.</p><p>Opsi D (<i>would not be uncovered</i>/tidak akan diungkap) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Selain menggunakan pola yang salah, kata kerja pasif pada opsi ini tidak tepat untuk disandingkan dengan subjek <i>‘they’</i> pada soal.</p><p>Opsi E (<i>would not have uncovered</i>/tidak akan pernah mengungkap) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong>. Susunan kata kerja pada opsi ini sesuai dengan pola kalimat pengandaian tipe 3 yang dibutuhkan.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah E.</strong></p>', 'Sedang', 'Conditional Sentences', '2025-06-21 03:32:27', '2025-06-21 03:32:27', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
(156, '<p><strong>Read the following passage carefully!</strong></p><p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>According to the passage, it can be hypothesized that the more …, the more ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah Inference &amp; Conclusion yang bertujuan untuk menarik kesimpulan atau dugaan baru berdasarkan isi teks di atas. Kata kunci yang harus diikuti adalah <i>“the more …, the more ….”</i> (semakin …, maka semakin ….).</p><p>Opsi A (semakin terlatih para peserta, semakin sering mereka melakukan olahraga ekstrim) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Tidak terdapat informasi yang mendukung bahwa intensitas berolahraga (ekstrim) seseorang berhubungan dengan semakin mahirnya mereka dalam olahraga tersebut, sehingga dugaan ini tidak dapat dibuktikan kebenarannya.</p><p>Opsi B (semakin banyak adrenalin yang mereka rasakan, semakin terlatih para pelaku olahraga ekstrim tersebut) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Tidak terdapat informasi dalam teks yang mendukung hubungan antara adrenalin dengan keterampilan berolahraga ekstrim seseorang.</p><p>Opsi C (semakin termotivasi para peserta, semakin mereka enggan untuk mengikuti penelitian) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Teks di atas tidak menyebutkan keengganan peserta dalam penelitian yang dipimpin oleh Professor Schweitzer.</p><p>Opsi D (semakin ekstrim olahraga tersebut, semakin para peserta menikmatinya) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong>. Pada paragraf 2, disebutkan beberapa contoh olahraga ekstrim dan bagaimana para peserta menikmati olahraga tersebut. Seperti BASE jumpers yang dapat melihat semua warna bebatuan ketika meluncur dengan kecepatan 300km/jam, atau seperti pendaki yang merasa melayang dan berdansa dengan bebatuan yang mereka daki <i>(BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock)</i>. Kita dapat menarik kesimpulan bahwa para peserta ini akan semakin menikmati olahraga yang semakin ekstrim karena pengalaman, sensasi, dan adrenalin yang hanya bisa mereka rasakan ketika melakukan olahraga tersebut.</p><p>Opsi E (semakin banyak resiko dari olahraga tersebut, semakin tidak bertanggung jawab para peserta) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pernyataan ini bertentangan dengan isi teks yang menyebutkan bahwa pelaku olahraga ekstrim ini merupakan individu yang terampil dan paham benar atas kemampuan diri, aktivitas, dan lingkungan tempat olahraga ekstrim tersebut dilakukan <i>(They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment)</i>. Kalimat tersebut menunjukkan bahwa mereka pastilah orang-orang yang bertanggung jawab atas apa yang mereka lakukan.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', 'Mudah', 'Inference & Conclusion', '2025-06-21 03:33:50', '2025-06-21 03:34:50', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
(157, '<p><strong>Read the following passage carefully!</strong></p><p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>The author would apparently agree that the phenomenon of extreme sports and their participants discussed in the passage is similar to the phenomenon between ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Inference &amp; Conclusion</i>. Kita diminta untuk menemukan analogi yang tepat antara olahraga ekstrim dan pelaku/pesertanya.</p><p>Hubungan antara olahraga ekstrim dan olahragawan/ti yang melakukannya dapat kita susun sebagai berikut:</p><p>(1) Tidak semua orang mampu dan mau melakukan olahraga ekstrim.</p><p>(2) Olahraga ekstrim hanya boleh dilakukan oleh profesional yang ahli di bidangnya.</p><p>(3) Orang-orang melakukan olahraga ekstrim untuk mendapatkan kenikmatan yang meningkatkan kualitas hidup mereka.</p><p>Opsi A (gigi dan dokter gigi) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Meskipun seorang dokter gigi harus melalui pendidikan dan pelatihan yang lama, dokter gigi adalah sebuah profesi. Hubungan ini tidak menghasilkan dampak yang serupa seperti hubungan olahraga ekstrim dan pelakunya sesuai poin 3.</p><p>Opsi B (mainan dan murid) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. ‘Mainan’ tidak hanya bisa dimainkan oleh murid, dan tidak perlu menjadi murid untuk bisa bermain.</p><p>Opsi C (gim dan pengembang software) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Meskipun benar pengembang software dapat menciptakan gim, tapi profesi itu tidak hanya diraih semata-mata untuk membuat gim.</p><p>Opsi D (piano dan pianis) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong>. Pianis adalah orang yang terampil dan mahir dalam memainkan piano, dan dampak yang dihasilkan oleh hubungan keduanya adalah kesenangan dan kenikmatan memainkan lagu atau partitur lain lewat piano.</p><p>Opsi E (buku dan penerbit) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Hubungan antara buku akan lebih eksklusif apabila dipasangkan dengan penulis dibanding dengan penerbitnya.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', 'Sedang', 'Inference & Conclusion', '2025-06-21 03:36:26', '2025-06-21 03:36:26', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
(158, '<p><strong>Read the following passage carefully!</strong></p><p>Researchers have debunked the myth that extreme sportsmen and women are adrenalin junkies with a death wish. According to Professor Brymer from Leeds Beckett University, there had been a gross misunderstanding of what motivates people to take part in extreme sports. Many wrote it off as an activity for adrenalin junkies.</p><p>His research has shown people who engage in extreme sports are anything but irresponsible risk-takers with a death wish. They are highly trained individuals with a deep knowledge of themselves, the activity and the environment. They usually do it to have a life-enhancing experience. For example, BASE jumpers talk about being able to see all the colours and nooks and crannies of the rock as they zoom past at 300km/h. Meanwhile, extreme climbers feel like they are floating and dancing with the rock.</p><p>Professor Schweitzer said understanding motivations for extreme sports were important to understanding humans. In fact, extreme sports participation facilitates more positive psychological experiences and expresses human values. These include humility, harmony, creativity, spirituality and a vital sense of self.</p><p>He added that extreme sports participants found it hard to put their experiences into words. Thus, the research project had taken a new approach to understanding the data. His research team did not employ a theory-based approach which may make judgements that do not reflect the lived experience of extreme sports participants. Instead, they took a phenomenological approach. By doing so, they were able to conceptualize such experiences. They could also investigate the choices to engage in activity which may lead to death. However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human.</p><p><i>Adapted from https://www.sciencedaily.com/</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The option that best completes the last sentence of the passage is ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Cohesion &amp; Coherence</i> yang bertujuan untuk menemukan kalimat yang tepat untuk melengkapi bagian rumpang di akhir teks.</p><p>Bagian rumpang di akhir berbunyi <i>“However, such experiences have been shown to be affirmative of life and the potential for transformation. Extreme sports have the potential to induce powerful states of consciousness … and provide a further glimpse into what it means to be human”</i>. Beberapa kalimat ini berfokus pada pembahasan dampak positif dari olahraga ekstrim yang dapat memberikan potensi untuk memicu kesadaran diri dan pengertian atas makna menjadi seorang manusia. Bagian rumpang akan tepat diisi oleh kalimat yang memiliki tema bahasan yang sama.</p><p>Opsi A (olahraga ekstrim mengeluarkan emosi negatif dan trauma masa lalu) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Bahasan tentang emosi negatif dan trauma memiliki cakupan yang berbeda dari bahasan pada bagian akhir teks tentang dampak olahraga ekstrim yang menunjang pengalaman hidup seseorang.</p><p>Opsi B (inilah di mana peserta meningkatkan keterampilan olahraga mereka) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Bagian akhir teks tidak membahas tentang keterampilan olahraga (ekstrim) dan cara melatihnya.</p><p>Opsi C (olahraga ekstrim memungkinkan pesertanya untuk lari dari rasa bosan di tempat kerja) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Cakupan tema pada opsi ini jauh berbeda dari bagian akhir teks yang ditanyakan.</p><p>Opsi D (pengalaman ini meningkatkan hidup para pelaku olahraga ekstrim tersebut) adalah jawaban yang <strong>tepat</strong>. Pernyataan tentang <i>‘life-enhancing experience’</i> pada opsi ini sesuai dengan bahasan pada bagian akhir teks.</p><p>Opsi E (olahraga ekstrim membawa latihan/kegiatan olahraga ke pandangan lain tentang kemanusiaan) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Bahasan ini sama dengan kalimat terakhir pada teks di atas, sehingga tidak bisa digunakan untuk melengkapi bagian rumpangnya.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', 'Sedang', 'Cohesion & Coherence', '2025-06-21 03:38:21', '2025-06-21 03:38:21', NULL, 7, 32, 2, 'Diterima', NULL),
