(341, '<p><strong>(1)</strong> Television was once the newest technology in our homes, and then came videos and computers. Today’s children are growing up in a rapidly changing digital age that is far different from their parents. A variety of technologies are all around in our homes, offices, and schools. When used wisely, technology and media can support learning and relationships. Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers.</p><p><strong>(2)</strong> Based on some evidence by research, there has never been more important time to apply principles of development and learning when considering the use of cutting-edge technologies and new media as the so-called interactive media. Interactive media refers to digital and analog materials, including software programs, applications (apps), some children’s television programming, e-books, the internet, and other forms of content designed to facilitate active and creative use by young children and to encourage social engagement with other children and adults.</p><p><strong>(3)</strong> When the integration of technology and interactive media in early childhood programs is built upon solid developmental foundations, and early childhood professionals are aware of both the challenges and the opportunities, educators are positioned to improve program quality by intentionally leveraging the potential of technology and media for the benefit of every child.</p><p><strong>(4)</strong> This statement provides guidance for early childhood educators about the use of technology and interactive media in ways that can optimize opportunities for young children’s development. In this statement, the definition of technology tools encompasses a broad range of digital devices such as computers, tablets, multi-touch screens, interactive whiteboards, mobile devices, cameras, audio recorders, electronic toys, games, e-book readers, and older analog devices still being used such as tape recorders, record and cassette players, projectors, and microscopes.</p><p><strong>(5)</strong> By appropriately and intentionally using the technology of his day - broadcast television - to connect with each individual child and with parents and families, it is demonstrated the positive potential of using technology and media in ways that are grounded in principles of child development.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: https://issuu.com/naeyc/docs/ps_technology_issuu_may2012)</i></p><p>The author would apparently agree on the idea that ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe pertanyaan di atas adalah <i>Author’s Opinion</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari tahu gagasan yang merupakan opini penulis.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (Media digital dapat membahayakan pembelajaran dan hubungan) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Terdapat salah satu kalimat pada paragraf pertama yang memperlihatkan bahwa media digital justru dapat mendukung pembelajaran dan hubungan. Kalimat tersebut berbunyi, <i>“When used wisely, technology and media can support learning and relationships”</i> (Ketika digunakan dengan bijak, teknologi dan media dapat mendukung pembelajaran dan hubungan).</p><p>Opsi B (Teknologi memberikan pengalaman yang menyenangkan bagi anak-anak) <strong>tepat</strong>. Berdasarkan kalimat <i>“Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers”</i> (Pengalaman bersama yang menyenangkan dan menarik yang mengoptimalkan potensi belajar dan perkembangan anak-anak dapat mendukung hubungan anak-anak, baik dengan orang dewasa maupun teman-temannya), terlihat bahwa teknologi dapat menjadi media yang bermanfaat bagi perkembangan anak-anak.</p><p>Opsi C (Teknologi akan memberikan lebih banyak hal baik daripada hal membahayakan jika digunakan secara bijak) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>.</p><p>Opsi D (Teknologi dapat mempengaruhi hubungan antara anak-anak dan teman-temannya) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Berdasarkan teks di atas, anak-anak tidak hanya dapat meningkatkan kemampuan bersosialisasi mereka dengan teman-temannya, tetapi juga dengan orang dewasa.</p><p>Opsi E (Teknologi meminimalisir potensi belajar dan perkembangan anak-anak dengan orang lain) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pernyataan ini bernilai keliru karena bertolak belakang dengan bacaan di atas. Bacaan tersebut menyebutkan bahwa teknologi justru mengoptimalkan proses belajar dan bersosialisasi mereka, seperti yang disebutkan pada kalimat <i>””Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers” (Pengalaman bersama yang menyenangkan dan menarik yang mengoptimalkan potensi belajar dan perkembangan anak-anak dapat mendukung hubungan anak-anak, baik dengan orang dewasa maupun teman-temannya),”</i></p><p><strong>Maka, jawaban yang tepat adalah B.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Author’s Opinion', '2025-06-30 03:47:43', '2025-06-30 03:47:43', NULL, 7, 35, 7, 'Diterima', NULL),
(342, '<p><strong>(1)</strong> Television was once the newest technology in our homes, and then came videos and computers. Today’s children are growing up in a rapidly changing digital age that is far different from their parents. A variety of technologies are all around in our homes, offices, and schools. When used wisely, technology and media can support learning and relationships. Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers.</p><p><strong>(2)</strong> Based on some evidence by research, there has never been more important time to apply principles of development and learning when considering the use of cutting-edge technologies and new media as the so-called interactive media. Interactive media refers to digital and analog materials, including software programs, applications (apps), some children’s television programming, e-books, the internet, and other forms of content designed to facilitate active and creative use by young children and to encourage social engagement with other children and adults.</p><p><strong>(3)</strong> When the integration of technology and interactive media in early childhood programs is built upon solid developmental foundations, and early childhood professionals are aware of both the challenges and the opportunities, educators are positioned to improve program quality by intentionally leveraging the potential of technology and media for the benefit of every child.</p><p><strong>(4)</strong> This statement provides guidance for early childhood educators about the use of technology and interactive media in ways that can optimize opportunities for young children’s development. In this statement, the definition of technology tools encompasses a broad range of digital devices such as computers, tablets, multi-touch screens, interactive whiteboards, mobile devices, cameras, audio recorders, electronic toys, games, e-book readers, and older analog devices still being used such as tape recorders, record and cassette players, projectors, and microscopes.</p><p><strong>(5)</strong> By appropriately and intentionally using the technology of his day - broadcast television - to connect with each individual child and with parents and families, it is demonstrated the positive potential of using technology and media in ways that are grounded in principles of child development.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: https://issuu.com/naeyc/docs/ps_technology_issuu_may2012)</i></p><p>The author holds the assumption that ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe pertanyaan di atas berkaitan dengan <i>Author’s Opinion</i> untuk mencari dugaan penulis terkait teknologi pada zaman sekarang.</p><p>Opsi A (Berbagai bentuk konten yang dirancang untuk memfasilitasi anak-anak kreatif untuk belajar akan menantang mereka) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Berdasarkan bacaan di atas, penulis berfokus pada penggunaan teknologi dan media interaktif dalam perkembangan dan pembelajaran anak. Dengan kata lain, tidak ada bahasan terkait konten yang dibuat secara khusus untuk anak-anak kreatif.</p><p>Opsi B (Media interaktif merupakan sejenis media yang mencakup perangkat keras dan artefak pendidikan) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pernyataan tersebut bersifat fakta, sehingga tidak dapat dikategorikan sebagai asumsi sang penulis.</p><p>Opsi C (Penggabungan teknologi dan media interaktif pada program anak menyebabkan peningkatan kualitas program) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pernyataan tersebut bukanlah opini karena penggunaan teknologi dan media interaktif secara bersamaan berpotensi meningkatkan kualitas program.</p><p>Opsi D (Penerapan kebijakan perkembangan dan pembelajaran anak-anak merupakan sekunder dalam penggunaan media interaktif) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Dalam bacaan di atas, tidak terdapat pandangan sang penulis terhadap penerapan prinsip perkembangan dan pembelajaran anak-anak sebagai hal yang tidak diprioritaskan.</p><p>Opsi E (Teknologi dan media dapat digunakan untuk memfasilitasi pembelajaran dan membentuk hubungan yang lebih dengan anak-anak lain dan orang dewasa) <strong>tepat</strong>. Kalimat <i>“Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers”</i> (Pengalaman bersama yang asyik dan menarik yang mengoptimalkan potensi belajar dan perkembangan anak-anak dapat mendukung hubungan anak-anak, baik dengan orang dewasa maupun teman sebaya) menunjukkan bahwa pengalaman anak-anak dalam memanfaatkan teknologi dalam pembelajaran dan perkembangan diri dapat membantu mereka belajar bersosialisasi dengan teman sebaya maupun orang dewasa.</p><p><strong>Maka, jawaban yang tepat adalah E.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Author’s Opinion', '2025-06-30 03:48:36', '2025-06-30 03:48:36', NULL, 7, 35, 7, 'Diterima', NULL),
(343, '<p><strong>(1)</strong> Television was once the newest technology in our homes, and then came videos and computers. Today’s children are growing up in a rapidly changing digital age that is far different from their parents. A variety of technologies are all around in our homes, offices, and schools. When used wisely, technology and media can support learning and relationships. Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers.</p><p><strong>(2)</strong> Based on some evidence by research, there has never been more important time to apply principles of development and learning when considering the use of cutting-edge technologies and new media as the so-called interactive media. Interactive media refers to digital and analog materials, including software programs, applications (apps), some children’s television programming, e-books, the internet, and other forms of content designed to facilitate active and creative use by young children and to encourage social engagement with other children and adults.</p><p><strong>(3)</strong> When the integration of technology and interactive media in early childhood programs is built upon solid developmental foundations, and early childhood professionals are aware of both the challenges and the opportunities, educators are positioned to improve program quality by intentionally leveraging the potential of technology and media for the benefit of every child.</p><p><strong>(4)</strong> This statement provides guidance for early childhood educators about the use of technology and interactive media in ways that can optimize opportunities for young children’s development. In this statement, the definition of technology tools encompasses a broad range of digital devices such as computers, tablets, multi-touch screens, interactive whiteboards, mobile devices, cameras, audio recorders, electronic toys, games, e-book readers, and older analog devices still being used such as tape recorders, record and cassette players, projectors, and microscopes.</p><p><strong>(5)</strong> By appropriately and intentionally using the technology of his day - broadcast television - to connect with each individual child and with parents and families, it is demonstrated the positive potential of using technology and media in ways that are grounded in principles of child development.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: https://issuu.com/naeyc/docs/ps_technology_issuu_may2012)</i></p><p>Which paragraph(s) illustrate(s) the importance of technology and interactive media use that pays attention to the principles of child development?</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe pertanyaan di atas adalah <i>Author’s Writing Organisation</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari bagian dalam teks yang menunjukkan pentingnya teknologi dan media interaktif terhadap prinsip perkembangan anak.</p><p>Paragraf 1 merupakan paragraf pembuka yang membicarakan isu umum terkait teknologi yang berkembang dan dapat dimanfaatkan untuk perkembangan dan pembelajaran anak.</p><p>Paragraf 2 membahas pentingnya teknologi yang senantiasa berkembang terhadap perkembangan anak-anak dalam bersosialisasi dengan teman-temannya maupun orang dewasa.</p><p>Paragraf 3 menyebutkan bahwasanya jika teknologi dan media interaktif digunakan secara bersamaan, kualitas program perkembangan anak dapat ditingkatkan.</p><p>Paragraf 4 menyebutkan teknologi yang dapat dimanfaatkan oleh tenaga pendidik.</p><p>Paragraf 5 merupakan kesimpulan dari penjelasan terhadap pentingnya teknologi dan media interaktif terhadap perkembangan anak dan peningkatan kualitas program.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Oleh karena itu, dapat disimpulkan bahwa bagian dari bacaan di atas yang membahas pentingnya teknologi dan media interaktif terhadap perkembangan anak adalah <strong>paragraf 2 dan 3.</strong></p><p><strong>Maka, jawaban yang tepat adalah C.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Author\'s Attitu